    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n507" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλέγω</span></b> , only pres.:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">care, care for, be concerned</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινός</span> (acc. <i><span class="en">Il. 16.388</span></i>);
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλέγουσι κιοῦσαι</span>, ‘are troubled’ as
          they go, <i><span class="en">Il. 9.504</span></i>; usually w. neg.,
          abs. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κύνες οὐκ ἀλέγουσαι</span>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">careless</span> (good-for-nothing) hussies, <i><span class="en">Od. 19.154</span></i>. In <i><span class="en">Od. 6.268</span></i> equiv. to <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλεγύνω</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
